<div>		



<span class="section_title">2007 INTERNATIONAL CES KICKS OFF 40TH ANNIVERSARY WITH GLOBAL ARRAY OF THE HOTTEST CE PRODUCTS FROM 2,700 EXHIBITORS</span>

	<br><br>
	<span class="subhead">CES' Newest Venue, the Sands Expo and Convention Center/The Venetian, Contributes to Largest Show Floor in CES History</span>

<br><br>		
<strong><i>Arlington, Virginia&nbsp;-&nbsp;1/8/2007</i></strong>
<br><br>
The 2007 International CES<sup>&#174</sup> opens its doors today to a record-setting 1.8 million net square feet of exhibit space, as the show celebrates its 40th anniversary. Produced by the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA<sup>&#174</sup>), the 2007 International CES, the world's largest tradeshow for consumer technology, returns to Las Vegas January 8-11, 2007.  
<p>
 "With the largest exhibit space in CES history and a global array of 2,700 exhibitors set to debut their latest innovations, the 2007 International CES is gearing up for a phenomenal show," said Karen Chupka, senior vice president, events and conferences, CEA. "CES attendees will witness some of the hottest products emerging on the market including the latest in portable content, wireless and high-definition - reinforcing the 2007 International CES as the global 'must-attend' event for consumer technology."
<p>
 The 2007 International CES will feature the latest products and technologies encompassing more than 30 product categories including digital imaging, home networking, IPTV, mobile electronics, gaming and more. The CES show floor will span across the Las Vegas Convention Center (LVCC), the Las Vegas Hilton and CES' newest venue - the Sands Expo and Convention Center/The Venetian, the new home to the CES keynotes and high-performance audio and home theater exhibits.
<p>
 The CES show floor will house more than 20 market-specific TechZones showcasing the latest industry trends and emerging technologies. The Anytime, Anywhere TechArena, sponsored by Sling Media and located at the Sands/Venetian, will feature the latest in portable content shifting devices, and also will house The Download, ExpressCard, IPTV and Podcasting TechZones. Additional TechZones making a splash at the International CES include the Gaming TechZone, showcasing the latest PC and console gaming developments, the Robotics TechZone, which will debut the latest in robotics trends and the Vehicle Communication & Safety TechZone, sponsored by ITS America, featuring the latest in active safety systems.
<p>
        Some of the biggest names in the consumer electronics and content industries will take the stage as part of the 2007 International CES keynote addresses, including Microsoft's Bill Gates, Motorola's Ed Zander, Disney's Robert Iger, Dell's Michael Dell and CBS' Leslie Moonves. CES attendees will hear from these industry visionaries in The Venetian's Palazzo Ballroom, which will house all CES keynotes at more than double the capacity of past keynote venues. 
<p>
 The 2007 CES Industry Insider Series has an explosive line-up of speakers set to deliver their vision of the CE industry. The 2007 CES Industry Insider speakers include Cisco's John Chambers, Nokia's Olli-Pekka Kallasvuo and FCC Chairman Kevin Martin. Additionally, the Industry Insider's Pipelines Power Panel includes top executives from major satellite, cable, broadcast and telco companies.
<p>
        The International CES conference program spans hundreds of industry topics, with more than 175 conference sessions and 300 speakers featured at the 2007 show. Educating CES attendees on the latest CE trends, the 2007 CES conference sessions range from broadband advertising and digital photography to home networking and mobile entertainment. 
<p>
        Additionally, the highly regarded Innovations Design and Engineering showcase returns where the International CES honors the best designed and engineered products new to the market. The Innovations 2007 Showcase will be on display throughout CES at the Sands/Venetian, booth #68747. 
<p>
        Ensuring a quality attendee experience continues to be a top priority for the International CES. MyCES kiosks will be placed strategically throughout the show to help attendees find exhibitors, locate products and print a personalized walking map that shows the location of the exhibits and products they want to see.  
<p>        
        Navigation between the CES venues and around Las Vegas is also a priority for CES. To help ensure attendees can make their way easily to the Sands/Venetian, CES encourages use of its two shuttle bus routes - the Sands/Venetian hotel shuttle between each official CES hotel and the Sands/Venetian Express, which will travel between the Sands/Venetian and the LVCC. 
<p>
        For more information on the 2007 International during and after the show, please visit <a href="http://www.CESweb.org">CESweb.org</a>.
<p>
<b>ABOUT CEA:</b><br>
       The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) is the preeminent trade association promoting growth in the consumer technology industry through technology policy, events, research, promotion and the fostering of business and strategic relationships.  CEA represents more than 2,100 corporate members involved in the design, development, manufacturing, distribution and integration of audio, video, mobile electronics, wireless and landline communications, information technology, digital imaging, home networking, multimedia and accessory products, as well as related services that are sold through consumer channels. Combined, CEA's members account for more than $140 billion in annual sales.  CEA's resources are available online at <a href="http://www.CE.org">www.CE.org</a>, the definitive source for information about the consumer electronics industry.  CEA also sponsors and manages the International CES - Defining Tomorrow's Technology.  All profits from CES are reinvested into industry services, including technical training and education, industry promotion, engineering standards development, market research and legislative advocacy.

